a group are, basically.

00:36:31.107 --> 00:36:31.940
CAROLINE WEBB: Yeah.

00:36:31.940 --> 00:36:33.776
It's a really great question.

00:36:33.776 --> 00:36:35.150
I did write about
the individual,

00:36:35.150 --> 00:36:40.170
because I do think that it's
very hard to be a great leader

00:36:40.170 --> 00:36:42.550
unless you're managing yourself
as effectively as you're

00:36:42.550 --> 00:36:44.355
managing your teams
and your organizations.

00:36:46.836 --> 00:36:48.210
I quite strongly
believe that all

00:36:48.210 --> 00:36:50.670
of the techniques that
we're talking about today

00:36:50.670 --> 00:36:53.630
can be used with teams.

00:36:53.630 --> 00:36:55.980
It does take a
little bit of a step

00:36:55.980 --> 00:36:59.530
to decide that you're going
to run a meeting, perhaps

00:36:59.530 --> 00:37:01.845
which you run every week,
