ideal is, and what

00:37:07.196 --> 00:37:08.320
the steps are towards that?

00:37:08.320 --> 00:37:10.865
We just need to fix the problem.

00:37:10.865 --> 00:37:12.990
But I strongly believe that
all of these techniques

00:37:12.990 --> 00:37:14.340
can be applied.

00:37:14.340 --> 00:37:17.050
In fact, they become much
stronger and much more powerful

00:37:17.050 --> 00:37:19.530
when they become team norms.

00:37:19.530 --> 00:37:21.610
And I think you guys
are very experimental.

00:37:21.610 --> 00:37:23.230
You're willing to
try new things,

00:37:23.230 --> 00:37:28.200
and you're known for being very
exploratory in figuring out

00:37:28.200 --> 00:37:31.440
what can help people
be at their best.

00:37:31.440 --> 00:37:34.670
So I would encourage you to
try these things in your teams,

00:37:34.670 --> 00:37:38.285
to see what changes in the
quality of the discussions

00:37:38.285 --> 00:37:38.955
that you have.

00:37:38.955 --> 00:37:40.080
MATT BRITTIN: That's great.

